# Shared Utilities

Use these shared utilities to avoid code duplication. Always prefer using existing utilities over writing new boilerplate.

## Backend Utilities (`src/common/utils/`)

### Entity Assertions

```typescript
import { assertFound, assertOwnershipOrAdmin, assertSelfOrAdmin } from "../../common/utils";

// Instead of:
const bot = await this.botRepository.findById(id);
if (!bot) throw new NotFoundException(`Bot ${id} not found`);

// Use:
const bot = await this.botRepository.findById(id);
assertFound(bot, "Bot", id);

// Or use repository method directly:
const bot = await this.botRepository.findByIdOrThrow(id);
```

### Ownership Checks

```typescript
// Instead of:
if (bot.user_id !== userId && !isAdmin) {
  throw new ForbiddenException("You do not own this bot");
}

// Use:
assertOwnershipOrAdmin(bot.user_id, userId, isAdmin, "You do not own this bot");

// Or use BotOwnershipService for bots:
const bot = await this.botOwnership.getBotWithOwnershipCheck(id, userId, isAdmin);
```

### Pagination

```typescript
import { toPaginatedResponse } from "../../common/utils";

// Instead of:
return {
  data: items.map((i) => this.toDto(i)),
  total,
  limit,
  offset,
  hasMore: offset + items.length < total,
};

// Use:
return toPaginatedResponse(items, total, limit, offset, (i) => this.toDto(i));
```

### User Self-or-Admin Access

```typescript
import { RequireSelfOrAdmin, SelfOrAdminGuard } from "../../common/guards";

// Instead of manual checks in each controller method:
if (user.id !== id && user.role !== "admin") {
  throw new ForbiddenException("Access denied");
}

// Use decorator:
@Controller("users")
@UseGuards(JwtAuthGuard, RolesGuard, SelfOrAdminGuard)
export class UsersController {
  @Get(":id")
  @RequireSelfOrAdmin("id")
  findOne(@Param("id") id: string) { ... }
}
```

### Error Logging

```typescript
import { logOperationError } from "../../common/utils";

// Instead of:
this.logger.error(`Failed to save state: ${error.message}`, error.stack);

// Use:
logOperationError(this.logger, "save game state", error, { gameId, playerId });
```

## QA Monster Utilities (`tests/qa/monsters/shared/`)

### Environment Config

```typescript
import { getEnv } from "../shared";

// Instead of scattered process.env calls:
const baseUrl = process.env.API_BASE_URL || process.env.API_URL || "http://localhost:3000";

// Use:
const env = getEnv();
const baseUrl = env.apiBaseUrl;
```

### Authentication

```typescript
import { createAuthHelper } from "../shared";

// Instead of duplicating auth logic:
const authHelper = createAuthHelper();
await authHelper.authenticateAsAdmin();
const headers = authHelper.getAdminHeaders();
```

### Health Checks

```typescript
import { requireBackendHealthy, checkHealth } from "../shared";

// Instead of:
const healthCheck = await this.fetch(`${url}/api/v1/health`);
if (!healthCheck.ok) throw new Error("Backend not responding");

// Use:
await requireBackendHealthy();
```

### Path Parameters

```typescript
import { replacePathParams, parseEndpoint, DEFAULT_TEST_IDS } from "../shared";

// Instead of:
path = path.replace(":id", "00000000-...");
path = path.replace(":botId", "00000000-...");

// Use:
const resolvedPath = replacePathParams(path, { id: testId });
```

### CLI Runners

```typescript
import { runMonsterCli } from "../shared";

// Instead of 30+ lines of CLI boilerplate:
if (require.main === module) {
  runMonsterCli(new MyMonster(), "my-monster-type");
}
```

### Response Validation

```typescript
import { validateResponseShape, COMMON_SHAPES } from "../shared";

// Use predefined shapes:
const result = validateResponseShape(response, COMMON_SHAPES.paginatedResponse);

// Or custom shapes:
const result = validateResponseShape(response, {
  id: "string",
  count: "number",
  items: "array",
});
```

## When to Create New Utilities

Create a new shared utility when:
1. The same pattern appears 3+ times across different files
2. The logic is complex enough to warrant abstraction
3. The pattern involves common error handling or validation

Always add new utilities to the appropriate index.ts for easy importing.
